Summary: The Massachusetts Property Insurance Underwriting Association (MPIUA) also known as the Massachusetts FAIR Plan (Fair Access to Insurance Requirements) provides basic property insurance on eligible property for applicants who have been unable to gain insurance through the voluntary market. MPIUA offers policies under the Homeowners, Dwelling Fire and Commercial Property programs as approved by the Massachusetts Division of Insurance.

Assumptions & Requirements
Steps
Balance Update
Invoice Cloud will update balances in real time when the customer record is accessed.
Integrator webservice is reachable and functioning
Account exists in Invoice Cloud
Customer Record is accessed in Invoice Cloud
Invoice Cloud calls Integrator webservice
Invoice Cloud updates balance (if IC record is different)
Data Pump Payments
Invoice Cloud will post payments to biller in real time when the customer makes a payment.
Integrator webservice is reachable and functioning
Account exists in Invoice Cloud
Payment is made on invoice
Customer Record is accessed in Invoice Cloud
Payment is made on an invoice
Invoice Cloud calls Integrator webservice
Data Pump Voids
Invoice Cloud will post voids to biller in real time when the customer has a void.
Integrator webservice is reachable and functioning
Account exists in Invoice Cloud
Payment is made on invoice
Void is made on invoice
Customer Record is accessed in Invoice Cloud
Payment is made on an invoice
Void is made on invoice
Invoice Cloud calls Integrator webservice
Data Pump ACH Rejects
Invoice Cloud will post ACH Rejects to biller via daily BATCH file when the customer has an ACH Reject.
Integrator has STFP access and functioning
Account exists in Invoice Cloud
Payment is made on invoice
ACH Reject is made on invoice
Customer Record is accessed in Invoice Cloud
Payment is made on an invoice
ACH Reject is made on invoice
Invoice Cloud uploads files daily only if ACH Rejects exists 
Data Pump Paperless Enrollment
Invoice Cloud will post paperless status to biller in real time when the customer enrolls in paperless.
Integrator webservice is reachable and functioning
Account exists in Invoice Cloud
User enrolls in Paperless
Customer Record is accessed in Invoice Cloud
Customer enrolls in paperless
Invoice Cloud calls Integrator webservice

User Registration
User registration happens after BIF upload. Not all MPIUA users are necessarily IC customers. Only insured customers are users on IC.

Registered User Payment
A registered user is logged in and makes payments on an account.
Assumption:
User is already registered and authenticated
MPIUA stores Remote Authentication Token from Remote Authentication web service
MPIUA redirects to IC Portal Customer Portal Recent Bill Listing
CloudSSOConnect (redirect 8 = Customer Portal Open Bill Listing)
 
 
Manage Payment Methods
A registered user is logged in to MPIUA portal and navigates to IC screen to store, update or remove payment methods.
Assumption:
User is already registered and authenticated
MPIUA redirects (IC SSO Portal)  to Payment Methods screen
CloudSSOConnect (redirect 5 = Customer Portal Payment Options)

Required Options
Input required integration options below.
ID
Option Description
Details
41
Block Customer Portal from Email Updates/Deletes
By default, the Customer Portal allows a customer to update and remove an email address. This will block that capability. (MLS)
Turned on for SSO
42
Biller Portal - Edit Email Address
By default, changes to the email address are allowed. Unchecking this will make the Email Address field in the Biller Portal as read-only.
Turned off for SSO
61
RTDR - Block Payments on RTDR Failures
For billers with RTDR, if enabled, if the RTDR encounters an error and is unable to retrieve the current balance, the customer will not be allowed to make a payment.
Enabled
This setting prevents the customer from making a payment if RTDR encounters an error and is unable to retrieve the current balance.
64
RTDR - Override 6 Hour Previous RTDR Check
For Billers with RTDR, we normally would not pull a RTDR Balance if we had a successful balance within the past 6 hours. Enable this to Force a refresh.
Enabled
This allows for RTDR to force a refresh which suffices MPIUAs need to check for blocking payments after a payment is already made within the day.
152
Disable 24-hour payment check for RTDR
RTDR will not refresh balances on invoices with a payment within the previous 24 hours. When enabled, this option will bypass that check
Enabled
This allows for RTDR to force a refresh which suffices MPIUAs need to check for blocking payments after a payment is already made within the day.
153
RTDR Option 64 - Refresh Rate Limit
When using Option 64 RTDR Refresh Override this sets the rate in Minutes at which an account will be refreshed.
Enabled (5 Minutes)
This allows for RTDR to force a refresh which suffices MPIUAs need to check for blocking payments after a payment is already made within the day. Also gives 5 minutes for data pump to post successfully.
